# 8. 全力ライブ！

Rin: The show's about to start, Miku!
Miku: It sure is! Let's put on another fantastic show today, Rin!
Rin: Yeah! Let's make this the best show yet!
Miku: Oh, we need to remember to be careful, though. Our set list is different than usual today.
Miku: I wonder if it would be better to change positions a bit sooner right before the interlude of the second song.
Rin: You mean what we talked about that during rehearsal? We need to move to stage right as soon as the interlude begins, right?
Miku: Right! I think that will make it easier to move into the next part of the routine.
Rin: Got it! I'll try to be a bit quicker than you since I'll be coming from the opposite end of the stage.
Miku: Sounds good! Thanks!
Rin: All right, let's get out there and give it all we've got♪
Miku: Hi everyone! Thank you for coming today!
Rin: We hope you enjoy the show! Let's have some fun!
Miku: (Good, we're off to a great start! Time to move so we can get the crowd even more fired up with our interlude dance!)
Miku: (Huh? Rin should have started moving to stage right by now.)
Rin: All right, everyone! Let's hear those voices!
Miku: (What?! She hasn't moved, yet?!)
Miku: (Did she get so wrapped up in the moment that she forgot about what we discussed?!)
Miku: (In that case, I'll have to get her attention!)
Miku: (Rin! You need to move over here!)
Rin: Is everyone enjoying the show?!
Miku: (She's not noticing me at all.)
Miku: (Only one thing to do, then!)
Rin: So far, so good! Now it's time to...
Rin: (Hm? I feel like I'm forgetting something. Oh, that's right!)
Rin: (I was supposed to move to the other side of the stage! What do I do? My dance with Miku is going to—)
Miku: Rin! Over here!
Rin: Huh?! Miku?! What are you doing over here?
Miku: If I come over here next to you, then you'll be able to do your dance just like usual!
Rin: R-Right! Thanks, Miku! Sorry about that!
Miku: You ready, then?! Time to dance♪
Miku: Come on, everyone! Time to get those hands waving to the beat!
Rin: Are you ready? Okay, let's go!
Miku: Great job today, Rin. The crowd sure was having fun out there!
Rin: Y-Yeah...
Miku: Hey, Rin. What do you say we go say hi to those four after we...
Rin: .....
Miku: Hm? What's the matter, Rin?
Rin: Sorry about today. I completely forgot about the change.
Miku: Don't worry about it! You were focused on getting the crowd all fired up!
Rin: Yeah, but...
Miku: Let's just be more careful next time and put on another great show!
Rin: Okay. I will.
Miku: Shall we go backstage and do our post-show stretches?
Rin: I have something I need to do real quick. Would you start without me?
Miku: Okay, I'll be waiting!
Miku: Hey, Rin! Where are you?
Miku: That's strange. She said she'd be back soon.
Miku: I wonder where she went. We always do our stretches together after a show. Huh?
Rin: Mmm...
Miku: Is that Rin lying on the ground?! A-Are you all right?!
Rin: *Snore*...
Miku: Oh, good. She's just sleeping. Hehe. She must be exhausted.
Miku: Hm? What's all this spread out on the ground?
Miku: Wow, these are all notes on our past shows. She even wrote down her ideas on how to improve specific parts. Look at all the notes about just today.
Miku: She must always put in so much work thinking about our next show.
Miku: Thank you, Rin. I'll do my best to make our next show great, too.
Rin: *Mumble*...
Miku: Oh, I know. There's a blanket in the rehearsal room.  I'll go grab it.
Miku: I had planned for us to go say hi to everyone, but...
Rin: *Snore*...
Miku: I'd hate to wake her up. Maybe I'll go by myself this time.
Miku: Good night, Rin.
